.TH NETLOOM 1 "March 2026" "netloom 1.10.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
.PP
netloom \- a shared command-line interface for plugin-backed network APIs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.EX
netloom [GLOBAL-OPTIONS] <module> <service> <action> [KEY=VALUE ...]
netloom load [list | show | <plugin>]
netloom server [list | show | use <profile>]
netloom cache [clear | update]
netloom [--help | ?]
netloom --version
.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
netloom provides a common CLI surface for vendor-specific network API plugins.
.PP
The shared runtime handles plugin selection, profile switching, cache management, output formatting, logging, and generic request options. The exact modules, services, actions, and request fields available under netloom <module> <service> <action> depend on the active plugin and whatever API documentation that plugin discovers from the selected server.
.PP
For provider-specific behavior, use the matching plugin reference such as netloom-clearpass.md.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom load <plugin>: Persist the active plugin used by later plugin-backed commands.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom load list: List installed or configured plugins.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom load show: Show the currently selected plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom server list: List configured profiles for the active plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom server show: Show the current profile and the config files that affect it.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom server use <profile>: Select the active profile inside the active plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom cache update: Refresh the local API catalog for the active plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
netloom cache clear: Remove the cached API catalog for the active plugin.
.SH COMMAND MODEL
.PP
General form:
.PP
.EX
netloom <module> <service> <action> [--key=value ...]
.EE
.PP
Common actions:
.IP "\[bu]" 2
list: List a collection. Often equivalent to get --all.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
get: Retrieve one resource or, with --all, a collection.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
add: Create a resource.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
update: Patch an existing resource.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
replace: Replace an existing resource.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
delete: Delete an existing resource.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
copy: Copy matching resources from one profile to another when supported by the active plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
diff: Compare matching resources between two profiles when supported by the active plugin.
.PP
Modules, services, actions, selectors, and request metadata are discovered dynamically and may differ by plugin, server version, and enabled API surface.
.SH PLUGINS
.PP
Plugins provide vendor-specific authentication, discovery, payload handling, normalization, and documentation while reusing the shared netloom runtime.
.PP
At least one plugin must be selected before running plugin-backed commands:
.PP
.EX
netloom load clearpass
.EE
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--log-level=LEVEL: Set the runtime log level.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--console: Also print response output to the terminal.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--out=FILE: Write output to an explicit file.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--data-format=FORMAT: Choose json, csv, or raw.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--csv-fieldnames=FIELDS: Comma-separated field order for CSV output.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--file=FILE: Load JSON or CSV input for write or bulk-style actions.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--api-token=TOKEN: Use an existing bearer token instead of logging in through the plugin.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--token-file=FILE: Read a bearer token from a file.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--catalog-view=visible|full: Choose the visible or retained full catalog.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--limit=N: Set page size when supported by the endpoint.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--offset=N: Set a collection offset when supported by the endpoint.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--sort=FIELD: Set server-side sort when supported by the endpoint.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--filter=JSON|FIELD:OP:VALUE: Set a server-side filter when supported by the endpoint.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--calculate-count=true|false: Request total-count style responses when supported.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--encrypt=enable|disable: Control masking of secret values in output.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--decrypt: Disable output masking and show secrets in output.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--help or ?: Show context-aware help.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
--version: Show version.
.SH FILTER EXPRESSIONS
.PP
When a plugin supports server-side filtering, netloom accepts either shorthand expressions or raw JSON expressions.
.PP
Shorthand form:
.PP
.EX
FIELD:OP:VALUE
.EE
.PP
Common operators:
.PP
.EX
equals
not-equals
contains
in
not-in
gt
gte
lt
lte
exists
.EE
.PP
Common shorthand examples:
.PP
.EX
--filter=name:equals:TEST
--filter=name:contains:guest
--filter=id:in:1,2,3
--filter=enabled:exists:true
.EE
.PP
Common JSON patterns:
.PP
.EX
{"key":{"$eq":"value"}}
{"key":{"$ne":"value"}}
{"key":{"$contains":"value"}}
{"key":{"$in":["value1","value2"]}}
{"key":{"$nin":["value1","value2"]}}
{"key":{"$gt":"value"}}
{"key":{"$gte":"value"}}
{"key":{"$lt":"value"}}
{"key":{"$lte":"value"}}
{"key":{"$regex":"regex"}}
{"key":{"$exists":true}}
{"key":{"$exists":false}}
{"$and":[filter1,filter2]}
{"$or":[filter1,filter2]}
{"$not":{filter}}
.EE
.PP
Advanced examples:
.PP
.EX
--filter='{"name":{"$contains":"guest"}}'
--filter='{"$and":[{"status":{"$eq":"Known"}},{"enabled":{"$exists":true}}]}'
.EE
.PP
Shell quoting matters because JSON expressions are passed as strings.
.SH CATALOG VIEWS
.PP
Some plugins retain more discovered metadata than they expose by default. --catalog-view=visible shows the normal operator-facing subset, while --catalog-view=full shows the full retained discovery data.
.PP
Typical troubleshooting flow:
.PP
.EX
netloom --catalog-view=full ?
netloom --catalog-view=full <module> <service> ?
.EE
.SH OUTPUT
.PP
By default, netloom writes response files under its state and output directories. Default generated filenames include timestamps so repeated commands do not overwrite earlier artifacts.
.PP
Supported output formats:
.IP "\[bu]" 2
json: Pretty-printed JSON output.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
csv: CSV output for list-style data.
.IP "\[bu]" 2
raw: Raw text or binary output, commonly used for export and download endpoints.
